      <biogHist id="md5-2ec334f330d4323511eb2957c0cb50a1">
        <p>Pharmacologist, 1950-  .  Louis A. Pagliaro joined the University in 1977 as an assistant professor  of pharmacy and pharmaceutical sciences.  He was granted full professorship in 1988; he also holds  an honorary professorship in Educational Psychology.  Dr. Pagliaro's chief research fields have  been in clinical pharmacology, drug abuse and computer-assisted learning.  From 1982 to 1986 he  coordinated the University's Master of Pharmacy program; he has written five textbooks and  numerous articles.</p>
      </biogHist>
